quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  74,32,"Nay, by the moon"
  74,33,and by the night when it withdraws
  74,34,and by the dawn when it brightens
  74,35,"surely, it (hell) is one of the greatest signs"
  74,36,and a warning to mankind
  74,37,"to any of you that chooses to go forward (by righteous deeds), or remain behind (by sins)"
  74,38,Every person is held in a pledge for what he has earned
  74,39,except those on the right (true believers)
  74,40,in gardens (Paradise) they will ask one another
  74,41,about the criminals. (They will say to them)
  74,42,“What has caused you to enter into hell?”
  74,43,"They will say: “We were not of those who used to offer prayers"
  74,44,nor we used to feed the poor
  74,45,we used to talk falsehood with vain talkers
  74,46,and we used to deny the Day of recompense
  74,47,until there came to us the certainty (death).”
  74,48,(On that Day) no intercession of intercessors will be of any use to them
  74,49,Then what is wrong with them (disbelievers) that they turn away from receiving the admonition
  74,50,As if they were frightened donkeys
  74,51,"fleeing from a hunter, or a lion, or a beast of prey"
  74,52,"Nay, everyone of them desires that he should be given pages spread out (writing from Allah that Islam is the right religion)"
  74,53,Nay! But they don’t fear the Hereafter (Allah’s punishment)
  74,54,"Nay, surely, this (Qur’an) is an admonition"
  74,55,"So whoever wills (let him read it), will reflect on it"
  74,56,And they will not take heed unless Allah wills. He is the One deserves that mankind should be afraid of Him. He is the One Who forgives